USD::core cpi::y/y.note: Year-over-year change in BLS Core CPI (CPI-U less food and energy) reflects the 12-month underlying inflation rate. Hot core inflation can lift USD and yields and often weighs on XAUUSD; cool core inflation can support it.

USD::core durable goods orders::m/m.note: Core Durable Goods Orders measures the month-over-month % change in new orders for long-lasting manufactured goods. A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::core pce price index::m/m.note: BEA Core PCE price index (PCE excluding food and energy) is released in the Personal Income and Outlays report. As a key Fed inflation gauge, a hotter print can lift yields and often weigh on XAUUSD; a softer print can support it.

USD::core pce price index::y/y.note: Year-over-year change in the BEA Core PCE price index (PCE excluding food and energy) is closely watched for the inflation trend. Upside surprises can lift real yields and often pressure XAUUSD; downside surprises can support it.

USD::core pce prices::none.note: BEA Core PCE price index measures prices paid for goods and services purchased by consumers, excluding food and energy. A higher-than-expected reading can lift yields and often weigh on XAUUSD; a lower reading can support it.

USD::core ppi::m/m.note: BLS Core PPI measures month-over-month changes in selling prices received by domestic producers, excluding food and energy. A hotter reading can lift yields and often pressure XAUUSD; a cooler reading can support it.

USD::core ppi::y/y.note: Year-over-year change in BLS Core PPI reflects producer-level inflation excluding food and energy. Upside surprises can lift USD and yields and often weigh on XAUUSD; downside surprises can support it.

USD::core retail sales::m/m.note: Core Retail Sales measures the month-over-month % change in retail spending. A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::corporate profits::q/q.note: BEA corporate profits represent the portion of total income earned from current production accounted for by US corporations.

USD::cpi index, n.s.a.::none.note: BLS CPI-U index (not seasonally adjusted) measures the average change over time in prices paid by urban consumers for a market basket of goods and services. A hotter reading can lift yields and often weighs on XAUUSD; a cooler reading can support it.

USD::cpi index, s.a::none.note: Seasonally adjusted CPI-U index level from BLS, designed to remove predictable seasonal patterns in prices. Upside inflation surprises can lift yields and often pressure XAUUSD; downside surprises can support it.

USD::cpi, n.s.a::m/m.note: Month-over-month change in the BLS CPI-U index (not seasonally adjusted), tracking prices paid by urban consumers. A stronger print can lift USD and yields and often weighs on XAUUSD; a weaker print can support it.

USD::cpi::m/m.note: BLS CPI-U month-over-month change measures short-term inflation in prices paid by urban consumers for a market basket. Hot inflation tends to lift yields and weigh on XAUUSD; softer inflation can support it.

USD::cpi::y/y.note: BLS CPI-U year-over-year change reflects the 12-month inflation rate in prices paid by urban consumers. Upside surprises can lift USD/real yields and often pressure XAUUSD; downside surprises can support it.

USD::crude oil imports::none.note: EIA Weekly Petroleum Status Report covers U.S. crude oil imports alongside other petroleum supply indicators.

USD::crude oil inventories::none.note: EIA Weekly Petroleum Status Report reports U.S. commercial crude oil inventories.

USD::current account::none.note: Current Account reports the current account balance.

USD::cushing crude oil inventories::none.note: EIA Weekly Petroleum Status Report includes crude oil inventories at Cushing, Oklahoma.

USD::dallas fed mfg business index::none.note: Dallas Fed Texas Manufacturing Outlook Survey indexes are calculated as the share reporting an increase minus the share reporting a decrease.

USD::dallas fed pce::none.note: Dallas Fed Trimmed Mean PCE inflation rate is an alternative core inflation measure based on BEA PCE price-index data. A higher-than-expected reading can lift yields and often weigh on XAUUSD; a lower reading can support it.

USD::dallas fed services revenues::none.note: Dallas Fed Texas Service Sector Outlook Survey asks firms whether revenue increased, decreased, or was unchanged over the previous month.

USD::discount rate::none.note: Federal Reserve discount window primary credit rate is the interest rate charged on primary credit advances to depository institutions.

USD::distillate fuel production::none.note: EIA reports refinery and blender net production of distillate fuel oil (net production = gross production minus gross inputs).

USD::domestic car sales::none.note: US Bureau of Economic Analysis (BEA) reports US sales of domestic autos (vehicles assembled in the US, Canada, and Mexico).

USD::domestic truck sales::none.note: U.S. Bureau of Economic Analysis (BEA) reports motor vehicle retail sales for domestic light weight trucks.

USD::durable goods orders::m/m.note: Durable Goods Orders measures the month-over-month % change in new orders for long-lasting manufactured goods. A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::durables excluding defense::m/m.note: Census M3 survey provides monthly statistics on manufacturing activity; this series is durable goods orders excluding defense.

USD::durables excluding transport::m/m.note: Census M3 survey provides monthly statistics on manufacturing activity; this series is durable goods orders excluding transportation.

USD::eia refinery crude runs::w/w.note: EIA Weekly Petroleum Status Report includes U.S. crude oil refinery inputs (refinery runs).

USD::eia short - term energy outlook::no.note: EIA Short-Term Energy Outlook provides monthly and yearly energy forecasts and analysis.

USD::eia weekly distillates stocks::none.note: EIA Weekly Petroleum Status Report provides weekly estimates of distillate fuel oil inventories.

USD::eia weekly refinery utilization rat.note: EIA refinery utilization rate reflects utilization of atmospheric crude oil distillation units, calculated as gross input divided by last reported operable capacity.

USD::employment benefits::q/q.note: BLS Employment Cost Index measures changes in employers' hourly labor costs; this subseries focuses on benefit costs. Hotter compensation growth can lift yields and often weighs on XAUUSD.

USD::employment cost index::q/q.note: The Employment Cost Index (ECI) measures the change in hourly labor cost to employers over time, including wages and salaries and benefits. Faster-than-expected cost growth can lift yields and often weighs on XAUUSD.

USD::employment wages::q/q.note: BLS Employment Cost Index (wages and salaries) measures changes in employers' hourly wage costs using a fixed labor basket. Faster wage-cost growth can support USD and often pressures XAUUSD via rates.

USD::existing home sales::m/m.note: National Association of Realtors (NAR) Existing-Home Sales covers sales and prices of existing homes (including condos and co-ops) with regional breakdowns.

USD::existing home sales::none.note: National Association of Realtors (NAR) Existing-Home Sales covers sales and prices of existing homes (including condos and co-ops) with regional breakdowns.

USD::export price index::m/m.note: BLS US Export Price Index measures the change over time in prices of goods or services sold to foreign buyers by US residents.

USD::export price index::y/y.note: BLS US Export Price Index measures the change over time in prices of goods or services sold to foreign buyers by US residents.

USD::exports::none.note: BEA defines exports of goods and services as goods and services sold by U.S. residents to foreign residents.

USD::factory orders ex transportation::m.note: Factory Orders excluding transportation removes a volatile category from the Census M3 new-orders data. Strength can support USD and often weighs on XAUUSD; weakness can be supportive.

USD::factory orders::m/m.note: US Census Bureau M3 provides monthly manufacturing shipments, inventories, and new orders (often called Factory Orders). Strong orders can support USD and weigh on XAUUSD; weak orders can support it.

USD::fed bank stress test results::none.note: The Fed's stress test is a forward-looking quantitative evaluation of bank capital under a hypothetical macroeconomic recession scenario.

USD::fed barr testimony::none.note: Testimony by Fed Vice Chair for Supervision Michael Barr, often focused on bank oversight and regulation. A more hawkish policy tone can lift USD and yields and often pressures XAUUSD; a dovish tone can do the opposite.

USD::fed chair powell speaks::none.note: Speech by Fed Chair Jerome Powell.

USD::fed chair powell testifies::none.note: Testimony by Fed Chair Jerome Powell.

USD::fed chair yellen speaks::none.note: Speech by Fed official Janet Yellen.

USD::fed chair yellen testifies::none.note: Testimony by Fed official Janet Yellen.

USD::fed chairman bernanke speaks::none.note: Speech by former Fed Chair Ben Bernanke.

USD::fed chairman bernanke testifies::no.note: Testimony by former Fed Chair Ben Bernanke.

USD::fed goolsbee speaks::none.note: Speech by Fed official Austan Goolsbee.

USD::fed governor cook speaks::none.note: Speech by Fed Governor Lisa Cook.

USD::fed governor cook testifies::none.note: Testimony by Fed Governor Lisa Cook.

USD::fed governor jefferson speaks::none.note: Speech by Fed Governor Philip Jefferson.

USD::fed governor jefferson testifies::n.note: Testimony by Fed Governor Philip Jefferson.

USD::fed interest rate decision::none.note: Fed Interest Rate Decision sets the policy rate (the Fed). A more hawkish-than-expected message can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a dovish surprise can support it.

USD::fed labor market conditions index::.note: Kansas City Fed Labor Market Conditions Indicators (LMCI) are two monthly measures based on 24 labor market variables, covering the level and momentum of labor-market activity. Stronger conditions can lift USD and often weigh on XAUUSD; weaker conditions can support it.

USD::fed logan speaks::none.note: Speech by Fed official Lorie Logan.

USD::fed monetary policy report::none.note: The Fed's Monetary Policy Report is the semiannual report to Congress on monetary policy and economic developments.

USD::fed statement::none.note: Fed Statement communicates the policy outlook and guidance (the Fed). A more hawkish-than-expected message can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a dovish surprise can support it.

USD::fed vice chair brainard speaks::non.note: Speech by Fed Vice Chair Lael Brainard.

USD::fed vice chair for supervision barr.note: Speech by Fed Vice Chair for Supervision Michael Barr.

USD::fed waller speaks::none.note: Speech by Fed Governor Christopher Waller.

USD::fed's balance sheet::none.note: The Federal Reserve publishes its balance sheet each week in the H.4.1 statistical release.

USD::federal budget balance::none.note: US Treasury's Monthly Treasury Statement summarizes federal receipts and outlays, producing the monthly budget surplus/deficit. A larger deficit can weigh on USD sentiment at the margin; a smaller deficit can be supportive.

USD::fomc economic projections::none.note: FOMC economic projections (SEP) are collected four times a year and include policymakers' projections for the appropriate target federal funds rate path.

USD::fomc meeting minutes::none.note: FOMC Meeting Minutes provides detail on the latest policy meeting (the Fed). A more hawkish-than-expected message can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a dovish surprise can support it.

USD::fomc member stanley fischer speaks:.note: Speech by Fed official Stanley Fischer.

USD::fomc press conference::none.note: FOMC Press Conference provides Q&A and messaging after the policy decision (the Fed). A more hawkish-than-expected message can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a dovish surprise can support it.

USD::fomc statement::none.note: FOMC Statement communicates the policy outlook and guidance (the Fed). A more hawkish-than-expected message can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a dovish surprise can support it.

USD::gasoline inventories::none.note: EIA Weekly Petroleum Status Report includes total motor gasoline inventories.

USD::gasoline production::none.note: EIA reports refinery and blender net production of gasoline (net production = gross production minus gross inputs).

USD::gdp price index::q/q.note: GDP Price Index measures quarter-over-quarter % growth in economic output. A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::gdp sales::none.note: BEA Final Sales of Domestic Product equals GDP minus the change in private inventories, often read as underlying demand. Stronger final sales can lift yields and often weigh on XAUUSD; weaker final sales can support it.

USD::gdp::q/q.note: GDP measures quarter-over-quarter % growth in economic output. A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::global semiconductor sales::m/m.note: Semiconductor Industry Association (SIA) reports monthly global semiconductor sales compiled by WSTS (three-month moving average).

USD::gold index::none.note: The Kitco Global Index (KGX) is designed to determine whether changes in gold reflect actual value changes, shifts in the US dollar, or both.

USD::goods orders non defense ex air::m/.note: Nondefense Capital Goods Excluding Aircraft (often called core capital goods) measures new orders for business-investment goods in the Census M3/durable goods data. Stronger orders can support USD and often weigh on XAUUSD; weaker orders can support it.

USD::goods trade balance::none.note: BEA and Census report monthly trade in goods and services; the goods trade balance is goods exports minus goods imports.

USD::government payrolls::none.note: Government Payrolls measures the change in employment. Stronger-than-expected labor data (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; weaker data can support it.

USD::heating oil stockpiles::none.note: EIA Weekly Petroleum Status Report includes distillate fuel oil inventories, commonly watched as heating oil stockpiles.

USD::house price index::m/m.note: FHFA House Price Index (HPI) measures changes in single-family home values.

USD::house price index::none.note: FHFA House Price Index (HPI) measures changes in single-family home values.

USD::house price index::y/y.note: FHFA House Price Index (HPI) measures changes in single-family home values.

USD::housing starts::m/m.note: Census New Residential Construction provides data on new privately-owned housing units started, under construction, and completed.

USD::housing starts::none.note: Census New Residential Construction provides national and regional counts of new privately-owned housing units started and completed.

USD::ibd/tipp economic optimism::none.note: Ibd/tipp Economic Optimism is a diffusion index of business activity (50 = expansion). A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::iea monthly report::none.note: IEA Oil Market Report (OMR) provides data, forecasts and analysis on the global oil market, including oil supply, demand, inventories, prices, refining activity, and oil trade.

USD::imf meetings::none.note: IMF and World Bank Annual and Spring Meetings bring together central bankers, ministers, and other leaders to discuss the global economic outlook and international development.

USD::import price index ex petroleum::m/.note: BLS US Import Price Index measures the change over time in prices of goods or services purchased from abroad by US residents, excluding petroleum.

USD::import price index::m/m.note: BLS US Import Price Index measures the change over time in prices of goods or services purchased from abroad by US residents.

USD::import price index::y/y.note: BLS US Import Price Index measures the change over time in prices of goods or services purchased from abroad by US residents.

USD::imports::none.note: BEA defines imports of goods and services as goods and services purchased by U.S. residents from foreign residents.

USD::industrial production::m/m.note: Industrial Production measures the month-over-month % change in industrial output. A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::industrial production::y/y.note: Industrial Production measures industrial output. A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::initial jobless claims::none.note: Initial Jobless Claims is the weekly number of new unemployment benefit claims. Stronger-than-expected labor data (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; weaker data can support it.

USD::interest rate projection - 1st yr::.note: FOMC Summary of Economic Projections reports participants' projected appropriate federal funds rate for one year ahead (midpoint of the target range).

USD::interest rate projection - 2nd yr::.note: FOMC Summary of Economic Projections reports participants' projected appropriate federal funds rate for two years ahead (midpoint of the target range).

USD::interest rate projection - 3rd yr::.note: FOMC Summary of Economic Projections reports participants' projected appropriate federal funds rate for three years ahead (midpoint of the target range).

USD::interest rate projection - current:.note: FOMC Summary of Economic Projections reports participants' projected appropriate federal funds rate for the current year (midpoint of the target range).

USD::interest rate projection - longer::.note: FOMC Summary of Economic Projections reports participants' projected appropriate federal funds rate for the longer run (midpoint of the target range).

USD::ism - new york index::none.note: ISM New York Index is a diffusion index of business activity (50 = expansion). A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::ism manufacturing employment::none.note: ISM Manufacturing Employment is a diffusion index of business activity (50 = expansion). Stronger-than-expected labor data (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; weaker data can support it.

USD::ism manufacturing new orders index:.note: ISM Manufacturing New Orders Index is a diffusion index of business activity (50 = expansion). A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::ism manufacturing pmi::none.note: ISM Manufacturing PMI is a diffusion index of business activity (50 = expansion). A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::ism manufacturing prices::none.note: ISM Manufacturing Prices is a diffusion index of business activity (50 = expansion). A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::ism non - manufacturing business ac.note: ISM Non Manufacturing Business Activity is a diffusion index of business activity (50 = expansion). A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::ism non - manufacturing employment:.note: ISM Non Manufacturing Employment is a diffusion index of business activity (50 = expansion). Stronger-than-expected labor data (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; weaker data can support it.

USD::ism non - manufacturing new orders:.note: ISM Non Manufacturing New Orders is a diffusion index of business activity (50 = expansion). A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::ism non - manufacturing pmi::none.note: ISM Non Manufacturing PMI is a diffusion index of business activity (50 = expansion). A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::ism non - manufacturing prices::non.note: ISM Non Manufacturing Prices is a diffusion index of business activity (50 = expansion). A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::ism ny business conditions::none.note: ISM Ny Business Conditions is a diffusion index of business activity (50 = expansion). A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::jackson hole symposium::none.note: Kansas City Fed hosts central bankers, policymakers, and economists at its annual economic policy symposium in Jackson Hole, Wyoming.

USD::jobless claims 4 - week avg.::none.note: Jobless Claims 4 Week Avg. is the weekly number of new unemployment benefit claims.

USD::jolts job openings::none.note: BLS JOLTS program produces monthly estimates of job openings, hires, and separations; this entry is job openings.

USD::kansas city fed president hoenig sp.note: Speech by Fed official Kansas City FED President Hoenig.

USD::kc fed composite index::none.note: Kansas City Fed Manufacturing Survey composite index is a composite index based on diffusion indexes of five indicators: new orders, production, employment, supplier deliveries, and inventories.

USD::kc fed manufacturing index::none.note: Kansas City Fed Manufacturing Survey diffusion indexes are calculated as the share reporting increases minus the share reporting declines.

USD::loan officer survey::none.note: Federal Reserve Senior Loan Officer Opinion Survey asks banks about changes in lending standards, terms, and demand for loans.

USD::m2 money supply::m/m.note: Federal Reserve H.6 Money Stock Measures publishes M2, a broad monetary aggregate that includes M1 plus small-denomination time deposits and retail money market funds.

USD::manufacturing payrolls::none.note: Manufacturing Payrolls measures the change in employment. Stronger-than-expected labor data (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; weaker data can support it.

USD::manufacturing production::m/m.note: Federal Reserve industrial production release reports a monthly index for manufacturing output (Industrial Production: Manufacturing).

USD::mass layoffs::none.note: BLS Mass Layoff Statistics (MLS) collects reports on mass layoff actions that result in workers being separated from their jobs.

USD::mba 30 - year mortgage rate::none.note: MBA Weekly Mortgage Applications Survey reports the average contract interest rate for 30-year fixed-rate mortgages.

USD::mba delinquency rates::q/q.note: MBA National Delinquency Survey provides quarterly residential mortgage delinquency and foreclosure statistics.

USD::mba mortgage applications::w/w.note: MBA's Weekly Applications Survey provides a timely indicator of U.S. housing and mortgage market activity based on mortgage applications.

USD::mba purchase index::none.note: MBA Weekly Mortgage Applications Survey Purchase Index measures mortgage loan application volume for home purchases.

USD::michigan 1 - year inflation expecta.note: University of Michigan Surveys of Consumers reports year-ahead inflation expectations from its monthly consumer survey. Higher expected inflation can lift yields and often weighs on XAUUSD; lower expectations can support it.

USD::michigan 5 - year inflation expecta.note: University of Michigan Surveys of Consumers reports longer-run inflation expectations (often treated as a 5-10 year outlook). Higher long-run expectations can lift real-rate expectations and often weigh on XAUUSD; lower can be supportive.

USD::michigan consumer expectations::non.note: University of Michigan Index of Consumer Expectations summarizes views on personal finances and the economy over the near and long term.

USD::michigan consumer sentiment::none.note: Michigan Consumer Sentiment is a survey-based sentiment reading.

USD::michigan current conditions::none.note: University of Michigan Current Conditions component reflects respondents' appraisal of present market conditions and personal finances.

USD::midwest manufacturing::none.note: Chicago Fed Midwest Manufacturing Index (CFMMI) was a monthly estimate of manufacturing output in the Seventh Federal Reserve District states.

USD::milk auctions::none.note: Milk Auctions is a government bond auction. A weak auction can push yields higher and pressure XAUUSD; a strong auction can help ease yields and support it.

USD::monster employment index::none.note: Monster Employment Index was a monthly analysis of online job demand based on millions of job postings aggregated from career sites and job boards. A stronger reading can support USD and often weighs on XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::mortgage market index::none.note: MBA Weekly Mortgage Applications Survey Market Composite Index measures mortgage loan application volume.

USD::mortgage refinance index::none.note: MBA Weekly Mortgage Applications Survey Refinance Index measures mortgage loan application volume for refinancing.

USD::nahb housing market index::none.note: NAHB/Wells Fargo Housing Market Index (HMI) measures single-family homebuilder sentiment on a 0-100 scale; readings above 50 indicate most builders are confident.

USD::natural gas storage::none.note: EIA publishes weekly estimates of working gas in underground storage for the Lower 48 states.

USD::new home sales::m/m.note: U.S. Census Bureau New Residential Sales provides national and regional data on new single-family houses sold and for sale, plus price statistics.

USD::new home sales::none.note: U.S. Census Bureau New Residential Sales provides national and regional data on new single-family houses sold and for sale, plus price statistics.

USD::nfib small business optimism::none.note: Nfib Small Business Optimism is a diffusion index of business activity (50 = expansion). A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::nonfarm payrolls::none.note: Nonfarm Payrolls measures the change in employment. Stronger-than-expected labor data (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; weaker data can support it.

USD::nonfarm productivity::q/q.note: BLS Productivity and Costs reports labor productivity (output per hour) in the nonfarm business sector. Higher productivity can temper inflation pressure and support XAUUSD if yields fall; weaker productivity can do the opposite.

USD::ny empire state manufacturing index.note: New York Fed Empire State Manufacturing Survey reports a seasonally adjusted diffusion index of business conditions for New York State manufacturers.

USD::ny fed 1 - year consumer inflation.note: NY Fed Survey of Consumer Expectations reports the median one-year-ahead inflation expectation. Higher expectations can push yields up and often weigh on XAUUSD; lower expectations can support it.

USD::opec monthly report::none.note: OPEC Monthly Oil Market Report (MOMR) covers major issues affecting the world oil market and provides an outlook for oil demand, supply, and market balance.

USD::overall net capital flow::none.note: Treasury TIC data summarize cross-border capital flows, including net transactions in long-term securities.

USD::participation rate::none.note: BLS labor force participation rate is the labor force as a percentage of the civilian noninstitutional population.

USD::payrolls benchmark (12m)::none.note: Payrolls Benchmark (12m) measures the change in employment. Stronger-than-expected labor data (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; weaker data can support it.

USD::payrolls benchmark, n.s.a. (12m)::n.note: BLS annual benchmark revision aligns CES payroll employment estimates to Unemployment Insurance (UI) records via QCEW.

USD::payrolls benchmark::none.note: Payrolls Benchmark measures the change in employment. Stronger-than-expected labor data (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; weaker data can support it.

USD::pce deflator::m/m.note: BEA PCE price index (often called the PCE deflator) reflects changes in prices of goods and services purchased by consumers and is released in Personal Income and Outlays. Hotter PCE inflation can lift yields and often weigh on XAUUSD; softer inflation can support it.

USD::pce deflator::y/y.note: Year-over-year change in the BEA PCE price index (PCE deflator) reflects the 12-month inflation trend in consumer expenditures. Upside surprises can lift real yields and often pressure XAUUSD; downside surprises can support it.

USD::pce price index::m/m.note: BEA PCE Price Index is a key Fed inflation gauge in the Personal Income and Outlays release, covering prices paid for goods and services purchased by consumers. USD::pce prices::none.note: BEA PCE price index reflects prices paid for goods and services purchased by consumers (including some spending on their behalf). Higher-than-expected PCE inflation can lift yields and often weigh on XAUUSD; softer inflation can support it.

USD::pending home sales index::none.note: National Association of Realtors (NAR) Pending Home Sales Index measures housing contract activity based on signed real estate contracts for existing homes.

USD::pending home sales::m/m.note: National Association of Realtors (NAR) Pending Home Sales Index measures housing contract activity based on signed contracts for existing homes.

USD::personal income::m/m.note: BEA defines personal income as income received by persons from all sources, including compensation and transfer payments.

USD::personal spending::m/m.note: BEA personal consumption expenditures (PCE) measure the goods and services purchased by persons.

USD::philly fed prices paid::none.note: Philadelphia Fed Manufacturing Business Outlook Survey uses diffusion indexes: % reporting an increase minus % reporting a decrease.

USD::ppi ex. food/energy/transport::m/m.note: PPI Ex. Food/energy/transport (Producer Price Index, MoM) measures the month-over-month % change in prices received by producers.

USD::ppi ex. food/energy/transport::y/y.note: PPI Ex. Food/energy/transport (Producer Price Index, YoY) measures the year-over-year % change in prices received by producers.

USD::ppi::m/m.note: BLS PPI measures changes in selling prices received by domestic producers for their output (often from the first commercial transaction). A hotter print can lift yields and often weigh on XAUUSD; a softer print can support it.

USD::ppi::y/y.note: Year-over-year change in BLS PPI reflects producer-level inflation in selling prices received by domestic producers. Upside surprises can lift USD and yields and often pressure XAUUSD; downside surprises can support it.

USD::presidential debate::none.note: Commission on Presidential Debates (CPD) sponsors and produces quadrennial general election debates for President and Vice President.

USD::private nonfarm payrolls::none.note: Private Nonfarm Payrolls measures the change in employment. Stronger-than-expected labor data (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; weaker data can support it.

USD::qe mbs::none.note: QE (MBS) refers to the Fed's purchases of mortgage-backed securities as part of large-scale asset purchases.

USD::qe total::none.note: QE refers to the Fed's large-scale asset purchases, including Treasury and mortgage-backed securities, which expand its balance sheet.

USD::qe treasuries::none.note: QE (Treasuries) refers to the Fed's purchases of U.S. Treasury securities as part of large-scale asset purchases.

USD::real consumer spending::none.note: Real consumer spending is inflation-adjusted personal consumption expenditures (PCE) reported in chained dollars.

USD::real earnings::m/m.note: BLS Real Earnings reports inflation-adjusted (CPI-deflated) average hourly and weekly earnings. Stronger real earnings can support USD and often weighs on XAUUSD; weaker real earnings can support it.

USD::real personal consumption::m/m.note: Real personal consumption expenditures are reported in chained dollars (inflation-adjusted PCE).

USD::redbook::m/m.note: Redbook Research (Johnson Redbook Service) publishes statistics and analysis on U.S. retail and same-store sales trends.

USD::redbook::y/y.note: Redbook Research publishes U.S. retail same-store sales trend statistics.

USD::reserve balances with federal reser.note: Reserve balances are funds depository institutions hold on deposit at the Federal Reserve.

USD::retail control::m/m.note: Retail control group excludes autos, building materials, gasoline, and food services, and is used in constructing personal consumption expenditures (PCE).

USD::retail inventories ex auto::none.note: Census Advance Economic Indicators report includes monthly estimates of retail inventories (end-of-month levels, not adjusted for price changes).

USD::retail sales ex gas/autos::m/m.note: Retail Sales ex Gas/autos measures the month-over-month % change in retail spending. A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::retail sales::m/m.note: Retail Sales measures the month-over-month % change in retail spending. A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::retail sales::y/y.note: Retail Sales measures retail spending. A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::richmond manufacturing index::none.note: Richmond Fed monthly business surveys report diffusion indexes derived from survey responses from manufacturing firms.

USD::richmond manufacturing shipments::n.note: Richmond Fed manufacturing survey includes a shipments index summarizing firms' reported changes in shipments in the Fifth District.

USD::richmond services index::none.note: Richmond Fed monthly business surveys report diffusion indexes derived from survey responses from service-sector firms.

USD::s&p 500 index::none.note: S&P 500 is a stock market index tracking the performance of 500 large companies listed on US stock exchanges.

USD::s&p global composite pmi::none.note: S&p Global Composite PMI is a diffusion index of business activity (50 = expansion). A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::s&p global manufacturing pmi::none.note: S&p Global Manufacturing PMI is a diffusion index of business activity (50 = expansion). A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::s&p global services pmi::none.note: S&p Global Services PMI is a diffusion index of business activity (50 = expansion). A higher-than-expected reading (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; a weaker reading can support it.

USD::s&p/cs hpi composite - 20 n.s.a.::m.note: S&P Cotality Case-Shiller 20-City Composite Home Price Index (NSA, Jan 2000=100) shows monthly home price changes across 20 metro areas.

USD::s&p/cs hpi composite - 20 n.s.a.::y.note: S&P Cotality Case-Shiller 20-City Composite Home Price Index (NSA, Jan 2000=100) shows the year-over-year change in home prices across 20 metro areas.

USD::s&p/cs hpi composite - 20 s.a.::m/m.note: S&P Cotality Case-Shiller 20-City Composite Home Price Index (SA, Jan 2000=100) shows monthly home price changes across 20 metro areas.

USD::sec kashkari speaks::none.note: Speech by Fed official Sec Kashkari.

USD::seevol cushing storage report::none.note: Seevol Cushing Storage Report reports crude oil inventories at the Cushing, Oklahoma storage hub, the delivery point for WTI.

USD::semi book/bill ratio::none.note: Semi Book/bill Ratio is a government bond auction. A weak auction can push yields higher and pressure XAUUSD; a strong auction can help ease yields and support it.

USD::texas services sector outlook::none.note: Dallas Fed conducts the Texas Service Sector Outlook Survey monthly to assess service sector activity in Texas.

USD::thomson reuters ipsos pcsi::none.note: LSEG/Ipsos Primary Consumer Sentiment Index (PCSI) is a monthly survey of consumer attitudes on the economy, personal finances, savings, and confidence to make major investments.

USD::tic net long - term transactions in.note: Treasury TIC data report monthly transactions in long-term securities between U.S. and foreign residents; this variant includes swaps.

USD::tic net long - term transactions::n.note: Treasury TIC data report monthly transactions in long-term securities between U.S. and foreign residents.

USD::total vehicle sales::none.note: U.S. Bureau of Economic Analysis (BEA) publishes Total Vehicle Sales in its Supplemental Estimates, Motor Vehicles release.

USD::trade balance::none.note: BEA and Census report monthly trade in goods and services; the trade balance is the difference between exports and imports.

USD::treasury department report::none.note: The Treasury Bulletin contains narrative, tables, and charts on Treasury issues, federal financial operations, international statistics, and U.S. government financial commitments.

USD::treasury secretary geithner speaks:.note: Speech by Fed official Treasury Secretary Geithner.

USD::treasury secretary lew speaks::none.note: Speech by Fed official Treasury Secretary Lew.

USD::treasury secretary mnuchin speaks::.note: Speech by Fed official Treasury Secretary Mnuchin.

USD::treasury secretary paulson speaks::.note: Speech by Fed official Treasury Secretary Paulson.

USD::treasury secretary yellen speaks::n.note: Speech by Fed official Treasury Secretary Yellen.

USD::u.s. baker hughes oil rig count::no.note: Baker Hughes issues weekly rig counts as a barometer for U.S. drilling activity, including the oil rig count.

USD::u.s. baker hughes total rig count::.note: Baker Hughes issues weekly rig counts as a barometer for U.S. drilling activity, including total rigs.

USD::u.s. president biden speaks::none.note: Speech by Fed official U.s. President Biden.

USD::u.s. president trump speaks::none.note: Speech by Fed official U.s. President Trump.

USD::u.s. presidential election::none.note: USA.gov notes the process of electing a U.S. president takes almost two years from start to finish.

USD::u.s. small business health index::n.note: Dun & Bradstreet Small Business Health Index measures year-over-year small business performance through payment patterns and credit use.

USD::u6 unemployment rate::none.note: U6 Unemployment Rate shows the share of the labor force that is unemployed. Stronger-than-expected labor data (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; weaker data can support it.

USD::unemployment rate::none.note: Unemployment Rate shows the share of the labor force that is unemployed. Stronger-than-expected labor data (vs forecast) can lift USD and yields, often pressuring XAUUSD; weaker data can support it.

USD::unit labor costs::q/q.note: BLS Productivity and Costs reports unit labor costs (labor compensation per unit of output). Upside surprises can lift yields and often weigh on XAUUSD; downside surprises can support it.

USD::us commercial banks deposits::none.note: Fed H.8 release provides an estimated weekly aggregated balance sheet for all U.S. commercial banks, including deposit liabilities.

USD::us federal budget::none.note: Treasury Monthly Treasury Statement provides information on receipts and outlays and the flow of money into and out of the U.S. Treasury.

USD::us foreign buying, t - bonds::none.note: Us Foreign Buying, T Bonds is a government bond auction. A weak auction can push yields higher and pressure XAUUSD; a strong auction can help ease yields and support it.

USD::us leading index::m/m.note: The Conference Board Leading Economic Index (LEI) is a composite average of individual leading indicators designed to signal peaks and troughs in the business cycle.

USD::wasde report::none.note: USDA's WASDE report provides monthly forecasts for supply and use of major U.S. and world agricultural commodities.

USD::wholesale inventories::m/m.note: Census MTIS report provides monthly measures of combined retail, wholesale, and manufacturing activity, including wholesale inventories.

USD::wholesale trade sales::m/m.note: U.S. Census Bureau Monthly Wholesale Trade report provides national estimates of wholesale sales, inventories, and inventories-to-sales ratios by kind of business.
